        "comment": "From late morning the likelihood of wet avalanches being released will increase. As a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation wet loose snow avalanches are possible, especially in case of releases originating from very steep starting zones that still retain some snow. <br/> <br/> As the penetration by moisture increases wet slab avalanches are possible as the day progresses, in particular medium-sized ones. This applies especially in case of releases originating from shady starting zones, but in isolated cases also in case of releases originating from high-altitude sunny starting zones that have retained the snow thus far. <br/> <br/> Individual avalanche prone locations for dry avalanches are to be found on very steep shady slopes above approximately 2500 m. Especially transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack are unfavourable. The avalanche prone locations are difficult to recognise.",
